This paper is about a deep learning model for saliency detection in natural scenes. The model uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long-term recurrent neural networks (LSTMs) to learn saliency-related features and incorporate global spatial and scene context. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the model involves deep learning techniques such as deep neural networks and LSTMs, which are also relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
